cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with improving sequence learning with recurrent networks, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses pretraining and unsupervised learning, which are topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). The use of long short term memory (LSTM) networks is a common technique in neural networks and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions text classification tasks, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the classification is based on visual content.
